@rdhabalia 

I think the idea here is : if advertisedAddress is not specified, both zookeeper and bookie use `127.0.0.1` which it was using before; if advertisedAddress is specified (e.g. for testing in docker environment), all three components (zk, bk and broker) use the advertisedAddress. so I don't think we should use InetAddress.getLocalHost().getHostName() which would resolve to other ip address than `127.0.0.1`.

Hope this make sense to you.

